          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Historic trial</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-11-1.jpg" alt="Historic trial" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu took the stand in his corruption <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/middle-east/20241210-israel-s-netanyahu-prepares-to-take-the-stand-in-historic-corruption-trial" target="_blank">trial</a>, which makes him the first sitting Israeli leader to testify as a criminal defendant. His charges include bribery, fraud, breach of trust, and being accused of trading regulatory favors for positive media coverage and accepting expensive gifts. He denies wrongdoing, calling the case a politically driven â€œwitch huntâ€ against his policies.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The trial is held at a time when Netanyahu is navigating Israelâ€™s war in <a href="https://www.history.com/news/gaza-conflict-history-israel-palestine" target="_blank">Gaza</a> and growing regional <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/10/02/middleeast/israel-lebanon-regional-war-analysis-intl/index.html" target="_blank">tensions</a>. The protestors against Netanyahu demanded his resignation, and his former political allies refused to serve in government, while the supporters viewed the charges as the justice system's bias and overreach. Netanyahu rejected the proposal to step down and strongly criticized law enforcement, media, and the court. The testimony will occur six hours a day, three days a week, for several weeks.â€‹</p>
        </mj-text>
