          Following the ousting of President Bashar al-Assad, several European countries, including Germany, Austria, and Nordic nations, have <a href="https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20241209-european-countries-suspend-syrian-asylum-decisions-after-assad-s-fall" target="_blank">suspended</a> Syrian asylum applications. Germany has frozen pending cases due to Syria's â€œunclear situation,â€ while Austria is reviewing asylum grants and developing deportation programs. Greece is optimistic about refugee returns, and Sweden, Norway, and Denmark have paused asylum decisions, seeking clarity on the evolving situation. France and the UK are also reassessing their policies, with Turkey reopening border crossings for refugees.</p>
